Therapy-General significantly improved post-exercise interventions (P=0.037). 
There were significant improvements in the QoL subdomains of emotional 
well-being and physical, social, and cognitive functions.
CONCLUSIONS: Exercise interventions are feasible and safe in patients with 
metastatic cancer. Exercise interventions can improve QoL and prevent skeletal 
muscle loss during palliative chemotherapy.

